    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> in half and add to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Once fork-tender, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and gently mix together – these are your <strong>buttery potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
